&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Neuro Interventional Radiology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barking, Havering and Redbridge University Hospitals NHS Trust are pleased to announce that there is currently a vacancy for a full time position for neuro interventional radiology consultant as part of their long term strategy of increased services within their interventional department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Services that we are looking to expand in the lead up to the completion of this project will include a 24/7 Mechanical Thrombectomy Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Radiology department employs 352 WTE staff for modalities which comprise X-ray, CT, MRI, US, Interventional, Medical Photography, Nuclear Medicine and Breast Symptomatic and operate at various sites (QH, KGH, Fanshawe, Barking and Harold Wood).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Radiology asset includes the following: three CTs, three static + a rental mobile MRIs, 20 US rooms, 12 X-ray rooms, 2 Bi-Plane + a basic interventional machine, four mammography machines and three Gamma camera etc. The department will be investing in more modern equipment in the coming years including the following SPECT CT, MRI, Hologic – Tomosynthesis and new Bi-plane machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Radiology system includes PACS, RIS and Soliton, and the implementation of the new PACS in 2015 with the tin client allows seamless remote reporting thereby supporting flexible working to achieve work-life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sanjiv Chawda Job title Radiology Consultant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address sanjiv.chawda@nhs.net Telephone number Contact No: 6383&lt;/p&gt;
